KW  - Exchange rates
KW  - Risk premia
KW  - News
KW  - Interest rates
KW  - Asset pricing models
AB  - In this paper we study the relative importance of surprises in fundamentals in explaining unexpected exchange rate movements. Employing a unique survey dataset that contains matched exchange rate and interest rate expectations, we are able to derive a number of interesting conclusions. A variance decomposition of unexpected exchange rate movements into various components reveals that interest rate news is relatively unimportant but that changes in perceptions about risk premia and, more importantly, revisions of expectations with regard to future exchange rate levels are crucial in explaining unexpected exchange rate movements.
ER  - 

