AB  - This study examines the efficiency and characteristics of the nine major indexes of the Madrid Stock Exchange from 1941 through 1992. The findings do not support weak form efficiency among the General, Bank, Construction, Investment, Metal-working, and Chemical Indexes. Results of the Utility, Food, and Communications Index tests are not consistent.
