UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0378426694001006
KW  - Loan commitments
KW  - Maturity structure
KW  - Capital structure
AB  - This paper examines the benefits and limitations of loan commitment financing. Commitments enable firms to adopt more efficient liquidation policies. We demonstrate, however, that the limitations of commitment financing depend on a number of firm characteristics. In some circumstances, firms find long-term debt to be a superior alternative to commitment financing. This provides a possible explanation for why loan commitments are not universally utilized. By considering both the benefits as well as the limitations of loan commitment financing, we are also able to integrate loan commitment contracts into a model of optimal debt maturity.
